ResponseBody:
WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.000
Skills and Abilities. Batman has no inherent superpowers. He relies on his own scientific

00:00:07.040 --> 00:00:13.060
knowledge, detective skills, and athletic prowess. In the stories, Batman is regarded

00:00:13.060 --> 00:00:18.960
as one of the world's greatest detective, if not the world's greatest crime solver.

00:00:18.960 --> 00:00:23.680
Batman has been repeatedly described as having genius-level intellect, one of the greatest

00:00:23.680 --> 00:00:30.600
martial artists in the DC universe, and having peak human physical conditioning. He has traveled

00:00:30.600 --> 00:00:35.720
the world acquiring the skills needed to aid his crusade against crime.

00:00:35.720 --> 00:00:40.960
His knowledge and expertise in almost every discipline known to man is nearly unparalleled

00:00:40.960 --> 00:00:47.480
by any other character in the universe. Batman's inexhaustible wealth allows him to access

00:00:47.480 --> 00:00:53.660
advanced technology. As a proficient scientist, he is able to use and modify those technologies

00:00:53.660 --> 00:01:00.660
to his advantage. Batman describes Superman as the most dangerous man on earth, able

00:01:01.260 --> 00:01:08.260
to defeat a team of super-powered extraterrestrials by himself in order to rescue his imprisoned

00:01:08.300 --> 00:01:15.300
teammates in the first storyline. Superman also considers Batman to be one

00:01:15.300 --> 00:01:21.460
of the most brilliant minds on the planet. Batman has the ability to function under great

00:01:21.580 --> 00:01:28.580
physical pain and withstand mind control. He is a master of disguise, multilingual,

00:01:28.980 --> 00:01:35.980
and an expert in espionage, often gathering information under different identities.

00:01:37.380 --> 00:01:44.380
Batman's karate, judo, and jiu-jitsu training has made him a master of stealth and escape,

00:01:44.380 --> 00:01:52.100
allowing him to appear and disappear at will, and to break free from the chains of his past
